Private schools in Scotland maintain a history of academic excellence, and this continued in 2018 with another collection of outstanding results in the exams, which is only reinforced by individual and collective success in sports, art, music and other community subjects.
With more than 30,000 students in all of Scotland, these schools, represented by the Scottish Council of Private Schools (SCIS), strive to offer students and their parents the best level.
Private schools aim to prepare their students for higher education, for their chosen career and place as citizens of the world.
