At present, languages are having the same consideration as subjects such as science, technology, engineering and mathematics in private and all kinds of school programs.
A survey carried out by the UK Employment and Training Commission in 2014 indicated that the lack of language knowledge accounted for 17% of the reasons why employers have to fill their vacancies.
Thus, language skills are increasingly needed to prepare for youth for future careers.
These skills are essential in a globalized world, as there are more job opportunities that need languages.
Regardless of your chosen career, learning a second language will have a real advantage in the future with a life skills like this.
Being able to communicate directly with people from other countries will put a bilingual person directly at the head of the competition.
According to a YouGov survey of over 4,000 British adults in 2013, 75% didn't speak any foreign language well enough to keep a conversation, and French was the only language spoken by a two-digit percentage, in this case 15%.
