Knowing a number of languages, especially those of developing economies, gives children more opportunities to find meaningful employment.
In Scotland, the languages of education differ according to school.
Some schools focus on the more classic modern languages, while others become more important languages for the United Kingdom by 2020, such as Mandarin or Japanese.
Regardless of their children's interests, private schools always have several languages to choose and specialized teachers in this field.
Scottish private schools specialize in providing a learning environment that prepares children and teams with the skills they need to succeed, whatever the future may tell them.
We cannot deny that at present, in a global business environment, languages are still of vital importance to the future of the country, so this must be reflected in education.
