In a speech to the United Nations General Assembly, Minister for Foreign Affairs Walid al-Moualem said that conditions in the country are improving.
"Today the situation on the ground is much more stable and secure thanks to the progress made in the fight against terrorism," he said.
The government continues to rehabilitate the areas destroyed by terrorists to restore normality.
All the necessary conditions are now given for the voluntary return of refugees to the country that had to be abandoned due to terrorism and unilateral economic measures that affected their daily lives and their livelihoods.
The UN estimates that more than 5.5 million Syrians have fled the country since the war began in 2011.
Another six million people still live in the country and need humanitarian assistance.
Al-Moualem said the Syrian regime would appreciate the help he can receive to rebuild a country that is devastated.
But he pointed out that he would not accept conditional aid or countries that supported the uprising.
